               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate xml:lang="ar">رُبَّما حوالي ١٩٩٤</origDate>
                    <origDate notBefore="1983" notAfter="1996">Probably <hi rendition="simple:italic">ca</hi> 1994</origDate>.

                     The manuscript belonged to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11985PetrosGS"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title"><hi rendition="simple:italic">ʾAbbā</hi></t:roleName> Ṗeṭros Gabra Śǝllāse (also
                     known as <t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title"><hi rendition="simple:italic">ʾAnbā</hi></t:roleName> Makāriyūs)</persName>;

                     it contains various texts and accomodates his personal documents.
                     In the foreword (<locus from="121r" to="122r">fols 121r–122r</locus>),
                     <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11985PetrosGS">Ṗeṭros Gabra Śǝllāse</persName> indicates
                     that he finished the first part of <ref target="#ms_i4">Text IV (Missal in Tigrinya)</ref>
                     on <date>21 Sana 1975 <hi rendition="simple:smallcaps">EC</hi> (= 29 June 1983 <hi rendition="simple:smallcaps">CE</hi>)</date>,
                      in <origPlace ref="https://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q61">Washington, D.C.</origPlace>. The last work contained in the manuscript,
                     <ref target="#ms_i5">Text V (A Canon of the Coptic Orthodox Church of Egypt)</ref> refers to the Statutes
